INSERT INTO bytes.bytes (id, author_id, title, body, code_snippet, language, embedding, type, is_active, created_at, updated_at) VALUES (
  '694cdf6f-6202-45ad-8d36-1dcb49031a6e',
  '00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001',
  $escape$REST + WebSockets — Connection Lifecycle, Heartbeat, and Rooms in Node.js$escape$,
  $escape$WebSockets upgrade an HTTP connection to a persistent, full-duplex channel. Your REST API handles the handshake: client sends `GET` with `Upgrade: websocket`, server responds `101 Switching Protocols`, and the TCP socket is handed off — HTTP is done. From there, frames flow bidirectionally with no polling overhead.

Heartbeats prevent zombie connections. The `ws` library exposes native ping/pong frames: server pings every 30s, client auto-replies with pong. If `ws.isAlive` is still `false` on the next tick, call `ws.terminate()` — not `ws.close()`, which requires a clean handshake your dead client can't complete.

Rooms are just a `Map<WebSocket, string>`. On `join`, store the socket keyed to a room ID. On `broadcast`, iterate `wss.clients`, filter by room, and send only to live sockets with `readyState === WebSocket.OPEN`. No external broker needed at MVP scale.

Reconnection lives client-side: exponential backoff starting at 1s, cap at 30s, reset on successful `open`. Preserve a `clientId` across reconnects so server-side state (room membership, subscriptions) can be restored without treating it as a new session.$escape$,
  $escape$const { WebSocketServer, WebSocket } = require('ws');
const wss = new WebSocketServer({ port: 8080 });
const rooms = new Map();

wss.on('connection', (ws) => {
  ws.isAlive = true;
  ws.on('pong', () => { ws.isAlive = true; });
  ws.on('message', (raw) => {
    const { type, room, payload } = JSON.parse(raw);
    if (type === 'join') rooms.set(ws, room);
    if (type === 'broadcast') {
      for (const client of wss.clients)
        if (client.readyState === WebSocket.OPEN && rooms.get(client) === room)
          client.send(JSON.stringify(payload));
    }
  });
});

setInterval(() => {
  for (const ws of wss.clients) {
    if (!ws.isAlive) { ws.terminate(); continue; }
    ws.isAlive = false;
    ws.ping();
  }
}, 30_000);$escape$,
  $escape$javascript$escape$,
